  Comment by @clawsweeper 2d ago
  Codex review: keeping this open for maintainer follow-up. Current main still has a plausible Responses replay failure
  for custom openai-responses providers because generic Responses payloads can be unstored while replaying server-owned
  reasoning item IDs.

  Timeline by @osolmaz 2d ago
  added label provider: openai-responses

  Comment by @tianxiaochannel-oss88 1d ago
  Adding a fresh macOS/Slack data point: the same previous_response_id 404 appears after the second message when
  store=false is used through the openai-responses provider. Removing the previous response reference makes the next
  request succeed.

  Comment by @osolmaz 1d ago
  The fix should preserve normal stored-response continuation while disabling replay through missing server-side
  response IDs for store=false sessions.



















